answers.answer: I just reread this post and realized that I said "this is my first child."  Of course, she's not my first, but it is the first time my uterus has been stretched this much.  That's what I meant.

question: Hello, I'm currently 39w5d, but my midwives won't let me go overdue because of gestational diabetes.  They're going to start ripening my cervix with cytotec tomorrow, do a second treatment on Wednesday and induce, also with cytotec, on Thursday.  I have one experience with cytotec from a missed miscarriage but would love to hear anyone's experiences being induced with it.  This is my first child; no abdominal surgeries; the baby's head seems really low judging by the amount of pelvic pain I've had lately.  I'm getting contractions daily but they're not developing.  I've been doing everything I can to kick-start labor on my own, but time is running out.  Thanks from a daily lurker!
title: Cytotec induction stories?
